# Cyrius — Language Reference (Index)
# How to read, write, and reason about Cyrius programs.
# Replaces the monolithic content/cyrius/language.cyml (4144 lines, 73 entries)
# split during vidya v2.4.3 into 6 surface-area files.
#
# Compiler-internal patches, bug-pin retrospectives, and release-arc
# narrative were moved to content/cyrius/field_notes/compiler/ for later
# review and cleanup. Resolved patches were dropped — the fix is in the
# compiler now and no agent action is needed.
#
# Verified on Cyrius 5.9.42 (shipped 2026-05-08 — v5.9.x cycle
# CLOSED at v5.9.43 closeout). cc5 self-host byte-identical at
# 751,744 B (`c7a3ad41`); cc5_aarch64 cross at 448,032 B.
# Stdlib module count: 79 (was 78 at v5.9.0; v5.9.42 added
# `lib/regression.cyr`). api-surface: 2792 entries.
#
# v5.9.x highlights — closed at v5.9.43 (2026-05-08; 43 patches
# over 2 days):
# - v5.9.0: niyama 1.0.1 fold (8th sibling distfile, 6,664
#   lines, 5 regex engines: bre / re2 / pcre / fuzzy / vim;
#   niyama ADR 0011 Triggered).
# - v5.9.1: sovereignty pass kickoff. 743 LOC of bash audit-
#   dispatcher rewritten as `programs/check.cyr` (~700 LOC of
#   sovereign cyrius) + `lib/audit_walk.cyr` (new 78th stdlib
#   module). `scripts/check.sh` is now a 30-line shim.
# - v5.9.33-39: agnosys 1.1.12 `#derive(Serialize)` cascade —
#   chars + `str_builder_putc` (.37), Mach-O ARM64 fnptr ASLR
#   fix (.38/.39 paired: `lib/fnptr.cyr` macOS branches +
#   `aarch64/fixup.cyr` ftype==3 ADRP+ADD), end-to-end
#   `_macho_derive_serialize_gate` on ecb.
# - v5.9.40: cx Phase 2c parity — sub-byte struct field load,
#   struct-byval return, ESTORESTACKPARM + EFLADDR_X1 +
#   ESTOREREGPARM cx impls. New cxvm load16/32/store16/32
#   opcodes (0x44-0x47).
# - v5.9.41: tls-live gate conversion + `_network_probe_check`
#   + `_run_with_timeout` helpers. `.sh-conversion arc CLOSED
#   (0 `tests/regression-*.sh` remaining).
# - v5.9.42: `lib/regression.cyr` testing-stdlib carve-out —
#   22 public verbs covering display / buffer-scan / process /
#   network / SSH-cluster primitives. `programs/check.cyr` net
#   -364 LOC.
#
# Prior v5.8.x cycle (CLOSED 2026-05-05; 65 patches over 5 days,
# longest minor in cyrius history by patch count) delivered: slices
# (6-arc completion), effect annotations, sum types + exhaustive
# match, Result<T,E> + ? operator, allocator vtable, Unicode 17.0.0
# (NFC/NFD/NFKC/NFKD; categories; casefold), heap-map monotonic
# reorganization, lib/ + main_*.cyr structural refactor, stdlib
# foldin (sandhi-pattern: 6 sibling distfiles vendored into lib/ —
# sakshi/patra/sigil/vani/yukti/sankoch; mabda + agnosys held until
# v5.10.x Class B FFI work lands).

# ─── Core Reference (core.cyml) ─── 7 entries ──────────────────────
# What Cyrius is + how to use the toolchain.

# overview                — Sovereign self-hosting systems language; cc5 binary; capabilities
# syntax                  — Variables, functions, control flow, operators, structs, slices, strings
# compiler_architecture   — Module layout, compilation flow, codegen model, optimization pipeline
# development_loop        — Proven workflow for adding features (research → vidya → build → test → audit → docs)
# known_limitations       — Active gotchas and grow-the-cap rules
# porting_guide           — How to add a new architecture backend (aarch64 example)
# stdlib                  — Module catalog with key APIs and dep bundles

# ─── Language Features (features.cyml) ─── 18 entries ──────────────
# How to use specific Cyrius language features.

# multi_width_types       — i8/i16/i32/i64/u128 with width-correct codegen
# sizeof_operator         — Compile-time size constants
# unions                  — Shared-offset variant fields
# bitfield_builtins       — bit_get/set/clear/toggle, popcount, ctz, clz
# struct_field_widths     — Per-field type annotations and offset rules
# expression_type_propagation — Mixing widths and pointer arithmetic
# defer_statement         — LIFO cleanup at function return (per-flag exit-path safe)
# ifplat_directive        — Sugar for #ifdef CYRIUS_ARCH_<UPPER>
# enum_namespacing        — Enum.VARIANT in any expression context
# ref_directive           — Compile-time TOML loading via #ref
# ret2_rethi              — Return two values via rax:rdx + native multi-return
# continue_in_for_loops   — continue with forward-patch
# derive_str_fields       — #derive(Serialize) + #derive(accessors)
# secret_var_compound_ops — Struct init, &local arch dispatch, #regalloc, secret var, attributes
# slice_type_v58x         — slice<T> / [T] first-class type with bounds-aware indexing
# relaxed_fn_ordering     — fn definitions can appear after top-level statements
# tagged_unions_v58x      — sum-type syntax: enum Result<T,E> { Ok(T), Err(E) } with multi-arg + nullary tagged variants
# exhaustive_match_v58x   — match-coverage check + arm-tag dedup (warning, not error; opt out via _ =>)

# ─── Stdlib Modules (stdlib_modules.cyml) ─── 12 entries ───────────
# Per-module usage (APIs, gotchas, idioms).

# atoi_stdlib                   — Decimal string → integer
# f64_atan_and_math_lib         — f64_atan builtin and lib/math.cyr transcendentals
# base64_module                 — RFC 4648 encode/decode
# chrono_module                 — Time, duration, sleep, ISO-8601
# file_locking                  — flock(2) wrappers in lib/io.cyr
# csv_module                    — RFC 4180 parse/write
# http_module                   — HTTP/1.0 client
# patra_stdlib_module           — Sovereign SQL database in stdlib
# strstr_function               — strstr / strchr / memchr
# hashmap_str_keys              — map_new_str() for Str-struct keys
# fncall_ceiling                — fncall0..fncall8 ABI rules and C-shim decision table
# identity_lookups_musl_pattern — pwd/grp/shadow/pam (NSS-free)

# ─── Tooling & Formats (tooling.cyml) ─── 14 entries ───────────────
# Compiler binaries, CLI driver, dev tools, helper scripts, formats,
# env vars, flags, plugin/LSP wiring. Refreshed at v5.8.19.

# compiler_binaries              — cc5 + cross-compilers (aarch64, Mach-O, PE, cyrius-x)
# cyrius_cli                     — Top-level CLI driver verbs
# tcyr_test_format               — Assertion-driven test format
# bcyr_fcyr_scyr_smcyr_formats   — Bench / fuzz / soak / smoke harness formats
# cyml_format                    — TOML header + markdown body in one file
# cyrius_cyml_manifest           — Project manifest format
# object_directive               — object; — emit ELF .o relocatable (PIC)
# compiler_env_vars              — CYRIUS_* env knobs
# compiler_flags                 — cc5 / cyrius CLI flags
# lsp_and_plugins                — cyrius-lsp + plugin wiring
# helper_scripts                 — scripts/ shell helpers
# release_pipeline               — How releases are built and tagged
# audit_test_check_pipeline      — Local + CI gates
# minimum_compiler_version_pin   — `cyrius = "X.Y.Z"` in cyrius.cyml

# ─── Agent Guides (agents.cyml) ─── 3 entries ──────────────────────
# Read-this-first rules for AI agents writing or modifying Cyrius code.

# cyrius_for_agents       — Top-level rules every agent must know first
# tcyr_test_conventions   — How to write a .tcyr that passes both check.sh and CI
# agent_anti_patterns     — Recurring agent moves the user has called out as wrong
